🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we provision an Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) with both IPv4 and IPv6 support using Terraform. By enabling IPv6, the VPC becomes capable of supporting dual-stack networking, allowing resources to communicate using both Internet Protocol versions.

This project introduces modern cloud networking concepts and demonstrates how Infrastructure as Code (IaC) can be used to provision future-ready network architectures.

🎯 Objective
Create an AWS VPC using Terraform
Assign an IPv4 CIDR block
Enable Amazon-provided IPv6 addressing
Understand dual-stack networking
Learn the role of IPv6 in modern cloud infrastructure

