📌 Concept Explanation

Every AWS VPC requires an IPv4 CIDR block, but AWS also allows you to associate an Amazon-provided IPv6 CIDR block.

This enables a dual-stack network, where resources can communicate using either protocol.

                Dual-Stack VPC

          IPv4                  IPv6
      10.0.0.0/16         2600:1f18:abcd::/56
            │                    │
            └─────────┬──────────┘
                      ▼
                 EC2 Instance

This approach provides greater flexibility and prepares your infrastructure for future internet standards.

Why IPv6 Matters

IPv4 has a limited address space of approximately 4.3 billion addresses, many of which are already allocated.

IPv6 was introduced to solve this limitation by providing an almost unlimited address space.

Benefits of IPv6 include:

Vastly larger address capacity
Improved scalability
Simplified routing
Better support for modern cloud-native applications
Elimination of public IPv4 address scarcity

Many AWS services now fully support IPv6, making it an important skill for cloud engineers.

