🚀 Summary

In this project, we provisioned an AWS VPC with both IPv4 and Amazon-provided IPv6 addressing using Terraform. This introduced dual-stack networking concepts and demonstrated how Infrastructure as Code can be used to build scalable, future-ready cloud environments.

💡 Senior DevOps Insight

While many organizations still rely heavily on IPv4, cloud platforms are steadily moving toward broader IPv6 adoption. As a DevOps engineer, understanding IPv6 isn't just 
about knowing a new addressing scheme—it's about designing infrastructure that is ready for future growth.

When planning cloud networks, experienced engineers don't ask, "Do we need IPv6 today?" They ask, "Will today's design still support the business five years from now?"

Learning IPv6 early gives you a deeper understanding of cloud networking and prepares you for enterprise environments where dual-stack architectures are increasingly becoming the standard.
